rComments: This class is an easy A - great GPA booster. I recommend you take it if that's all you want. I didn't learn much in this class, I have only read the powerpoints and showed up to the final exam. This prof is disrespectful and  arrogant. I didn't feel like he wanted to teach or share knowledge, it's as if he was obligated to be there.

Not the most interesting class but definitely an easy A. The project, which is in 3 parts, represents 65% of the class. 
Get that GPA boost!
did not go to a single class. easy projects. easy final. easy A+.

Those who can't speak French, good luck. He takes his French lectures and directly translate them to English instead of finding the correct English word. So his tests are confusing as you are trying to figure out what he's trying to ask. If you understand French, take the final exam in French. Do the readings and go to class.

Prof. Beaulieu is an amazing lecturer. He does not read slides but rather uses personal anecdotes to correlate the material. The class itself is very easy. 65% of the class is a group assignment. I have no complaints with this professor I highly recommend him. If you are looking for an east GPA booster definitely recommend it.

Le pire prof que j'ai eu dans ma toute scolarité. Le cours asynchrone n'est qu'un ppt avec du texte, offert sans aucune explication ou contexte. Le cours en classe ne dure que 30 min car il passe la première moitié à faire des cours de morale ou raconter des histoires sans contexte. Vulgaire. Je regrette d'avoir pas drop, je n'ai rien appris.
Incredibly unprofessional, crude and uninspiring.

Would not recommend him for online, he doesnt post or hold live lectures. Only one at the end of the module. Also if u have social anxiety do not take him for in person, literal worst nightmare of a person

Easiest class I ever took, it was an easy A. Everything was asynchronous and there wasn't much to learn honestly, he gave us slides as the material- he rarely explained things (we didn't even have office hours) but the course was super easy and I never stressed abt it If you wanted a synchronous approach then I would not recommend him lol
His midterm wasnt well explained and when students asked for clarity he would be really rude to students. I would never take him again considering the lack of interest he had to teach.

He takes advantage of the fact thats its online, doesnt do any lectures kind of expects you to know what to do even though his notes are very point form. Nothing is ever specified and hes very unorganized. This class wouldve been fun if it was in person and if he took the time to explain his powerpoints.

This prof is not good a teaching online. Unorganised layout, hardy anything synchronous, no slides that present information, confusing assignments. Gave no resource for textbook and it wasn't available at the UO store. He posted blurry pages instead and deleted randomly. Rude to students on zoom and the expections/instructions are VERY unclear.

This is the second time I've taken Beaulieu. The class was an easy A, but there was quite a bit of work to do. There were 5 forums, 2 short assignments, 2 long assignments, and a final. We only had one zoom meeting at the beginning of the semester and had to be present for the forums, but other than that all you had to do was do your assignments.
Take his classes for a GPA boost. Absolutely loved him.

I liked how caring and funny Beaulieu was. He made the information easy to understand by using anecdotes and examples as well as the vocabulary he used. He also made it entertaining by walking all around the classroom. I really liked that there was only 3 assignments to hand-in as well as an online final exam so there wasn't really much studying.
Un des meilleurs professeur que j'ai eu.

I enjoyed taking this class, its an easy A elective and I learnt so much in this course. Make sure to get a good group, once you do, you're set for the semester. Professor Beaulieu is very kind, hilarious and knowledgeable. He's passionate when teaching and is very approachable. Definitely one of the best profs at uOttawa

This is an optional HSS class but I'm actually really glad I took it! 65% of your grade is a research project that you spend all semester working on but the deadlines are evenly spread out so it saves you less stress. Make sure you do well on the project, final exam is a small portion of your entire mark. Good GPA booster in my opinion. Goodluck!
What a gem! he's such a good prof and I highly recommend taking a class with him as the prof.

Francois jokes a lot but he is a very good and intelligent professor. The group project weighted a lot so make sure to get a good group. His quiz and finals weren't too crazy. Read the slides, skim through the textbook and apply common sense and you will be good

THIS MAN IS SO FUNNY!! His lectures are something you can't get bored of because hes always interacting with students and giving examples that are easy to understand. Lectures however aren't mandatory. Quiz is common sense, and the project makes up most of ur grade so find a good group, super easy. Does require to do reading for the final tho.

I love this guy. He's such a fun prof, loves to talk, but he still teaches the stuff you need to learn. he walks ALL AROUND THE CLASS, so no zoning out on Facebook or something. He's probably the best prof i've had in my 5 years at uOttawa and i'd take his class again in a heartbeat!!

Sermons for most of the class instead of actually teaching course material. It's entertaining for the first class or so, but frustrating after a while. On the plus side, it's an easy-A, but I didn't feel like it brought much to my education, which is the whole purpose of university.

Francois is an educated man real talk! He didn't want to bore us with slides and crazy notes so he kept it really simple and gave us stories instead. He's really loud and clear (BTW)! He also likes to walk around THE ENTIRE CLASS so try to be respectful but you can also multitask and do other work sometimes. If he taught another class I'D TAKE IT

Francois' lectures may be filled with random stories of his experiences or other rants, but it was kind of entertaining. His powerpoints barely had words but it was really all you needed to study!!! No textbook and his exams were common sense. Such an un-stressful course with him, I loved it. Really cares about his students!

He provides slides that do not make any sense, with weird hand drawings and french misspelling. Tests are nearly illegible, and make no logical sense . One example of a test question is: "True or False" This is my second time getting the HIV. Do not recommend his course if you care about the subject, but it is super easy marks.
